thread.title: DIARY - Today in Washington - Jan 17

author: Reuters Editorial
title: DIARY - Today in Washington - Jan 17

organizations.name: american petroleum institute issues weekly national petroleum

text:
ALL TIMES IN EST/GMT 0700/1200: The USDA issues weekly world rice price.
0915/1415: The Federal Reserve issues Industrial Production for December.
No set time: The Association of American Railroads issues Weekly Traffic of Major Railroads.
1400/1900: The Federal Reserve issues the Beige Book on economic conditions.
1600/2100: The Treasury Dept. issues Treasury International Capital flows for November.
1630/2130: American Petroleum Institute issues weekly national petroleum report. (Delayed from Tuesday due to the Martin Luther King Jr. Day federal holiday on Monday.)
